OL,3,CGrave of man who composed Welsh
OL,4,Cnational anthem restored
OL,6,FThe song we now know as Hen Wlad was
OL,7,Foriginally called Glan Rhondda. It's
OL,8,Fsaid the tune came into the older
OL,9,FJames' mind while walking the bank of
OL,10,Fthe river Rhondda.
OL,12,FThe song's popularity began to rise
OL,13,Fwhen it was sang at 19th century
OL,14,FEisteddfodau. It is also said to be
OL,15,Fthe first anthem sung at an
OL,16,Finternational sporting event.
OL,18,F"This is probably one of the proudest
OL,19,Fthings I've ever been part of,"
OL,20,FAngharad said.
